[1] Cholera - Haiti
Date: Fri 28 Jan 2011
Source: Agence France-Presse (AFP) [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2011/01/28/3123904.htm?section=justin>


The death toll from Haiti's cholera epidemic has risen to at least
4030 more than 3 months after the disease broke out in the country's
Artibonite Valley, the health ministry said. The number of cholera
cases in Haiti totalled 209 034 as of 24 Jan 2011, the ministry said.

The severity of the epidemic has diminished over time, but the
ministry's figures show that Haitians are still dying from the
bacterial infection, which can strike swiftly with intense diarrhea
and vomiting leading to dehydration and sometimes death.

--
