*****
[5] Cholera - Zimbabwe (Masvingo)
Date: Thu 20 Jan 2011
Source: The Zimbabwean [edited]
<http://www.thezimbabwean.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=36904:fresh-cholera-outbreak-in-bikita&catid=69:sunday-top-stories&Itemid=30>


A fresh cholera outbreak which has seen 60 people infected with the
disease and 4 people dead has been reported in Bikita. Masvingo
Provincial Medical Director Dr Robert Mudyiradima said tests had
confirmed that the deaths of 2 children, a man and a woman from Nyika
Growth Point were caused by cholera.

"We have dispatched our health teams to assess the situation and raise
more awareness on the disease," Dr Mudyiradima said. He said the
recent rains and a recent meeting of the Apostolic Faith members could
have contributed to the resurgent outbreak. "I am told there was an
apostolic sect meeting held near Nyika growth point. The church
gathering went for 3 days. The people there had no toilets and [no]
clean source of water."

--
